description: A small Romano-Celtic temple located at 54-56 Gresham Street excavated in 2006. It sits just south of the Roman amphitheatre next to the temple at 30 Gresham Street.
bibliography: Bateman, N. C. W., C. Cowan, and R Wroe-Brown. London’s Roman Amphitheatre: Guildhall Yard, City of London, London. Monograph 35. MOLAS, 2008.
Hall, J, and J Shepherd. “Places of Worship in Roman London and Beyond.” In Ritual Landscapes of Roman South-East Britain, 2008.
